; This is a build script for asset banks for the Sega Dreamcast[tm] 
;
; These tags may be hand edited as needed, the script builder utitity
; is there to write 98%-100% of the script. 
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; * Midi Files:
;
;	MidiFileType0			e:\code\mkscript\mixed\Short5.mid
;	Volume					127
;	GmMode					1
;	AssetEnd
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; * Wave Files:
;
; Certain items can not be determined from the wave files directly these 
; items will need to be adjusted by hand.
;
; The main tag that will be adjusted is the loop tag which controls
; sample looping. Set this to 1 for loop 0 for non-looping.
;
;	WaveFile				e:\code\mkscript\mixed\spaceLoop.wav
;	SampleRate				44100
;	Loop					0
;	Adpcm					0
;	AssetEnd
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; * Dsp Files:
;
; There are currently no supported arguments for DSP program banks.
;
;	DspProgramBank			e:\code\mkscript\mixed\patches.dsp 
;	AssetEnd
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; * Mtb (Sega Midi Tone Bank) Files
;
; There are currently no supported arguments for MIDI tone banks.
;
;	MidiToneBank			e:\code\mkscript\mixed\tonebank.mtb 
;	AssetEnd
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; * Unknown file type
;
; Files of any type can be packed into a katbank, these assets have
; 8 user arguments that can be retrieved via the bank API. The argument
; tags are signed 32 bit values:
;
;	UnknownFileType			e:\code\mkscript\mixed\Unknown.unk 
;	Parameter0				0
;	Parameter1				0
;	Parameter2				0
;	Parameter3				0
;	Parameter4				0
;	Parameter5				0
;	Parameter6				0
;	Parameter7				0
;	AssetEnd
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; The Tags Explained...
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Comments are preceeded with a ; (semi-colon) character...
;
; All tags are non-case sensitive, the caps are purely for readability.
; the format of the tags are...
; 
; Tag Argument 
; 
; The argument is seperated from the tag by any whitespace char, 
; i.e. space or tab
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Global header section
;
; BankFileName		fileName.kat
;
; This is the name of the file that will be created by the program mkbank
; the file name is an 8.3 file name and does not include a path.
;
; The extension is .kat (Katapi One Shot Bank) but is not restricted to that.
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; MidiFileType0		fileName.mid
;
; This is the midi file that is being added to the bank, the arg is an
; 8.3 filename with path.
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Volume		127
; 
; This is the master volume at which the sequence will be started. If a sequence is too loud
; in comparison to the others this is an easy place to turn it down. The range is 0-127.; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; GmMode		1
;
; This is used to tell the driver that the sequence is a GM sequence.
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; The following applies only to wave file type scripts.
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; WaveFile			fileName.wav
; 
; This is the soundfile that is being added to the bank, the arg is an
; 8.3 filename with path.
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; SampleRate		22050
; 
; This is the sample rate of the soundfile.
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; RandomPitchAmount	10
; 
; This is the random pitch percentage that will be applied to the sample rate
;
; i.e. a setting of 10 will cause a 22050 sample to play back at a sample rate
; between 24255 and 19845
;
; The default setting of this flags value is controlled via the random arg to MkScript.
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Adpcm			0
;
; This is the compression flag for the sound, if set to 0 the sound will
; not be compressed, if set to 1 it will be compressed with 4:1 ADPCM compression.
;
; The default setting of this flags value is controlled via the adpcm arg to MkScript.
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Loop			0
;
; IMPORTANT! This tag must be after the Adpcm tag as it will calculate loop points in frames
; for .wav files and needs the output bit depth to perform this calculation.
;
; This is the loop flag for the sound, if set to 0 the sound will not
; loop, if set to 1 the sound will loop front to back.
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; UnknownFileType			fileName.???
;
; This is a file of unknown type that is being added to the bank. The record will have
; all eight user parameters set to 0.
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Parameter0 to parameter7
;
; These are user parameter tags for an unknown file type. They may be set to any value
; you need with in the range of a signed long.
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
; AssetEnd
;
; This is the end of an asset record, this tag has no argument.
; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
; *******************************************************************************************
; The script begins here...
; *******************************************************************************************
; -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
